<font color="#FF0000">JUST TALKING</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jan 31 16:06:54 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
From reading the messages post here I can clearly see many of my fellow VietNam Veterans are still having trouble readjusting to the WORLD.  People ask me why!  And all that I can think of is that our VietNam Vets fought in a very unpopular war.  During a time when the USA was going through a cultural revolution.  The difference between the VietNam war and World War II, is this; In vietnam we sent 18 and 19 year children into combat, In World War II we sent 18 and 19 year old men into combat.  The older folks were prepared anf the younger ones were not.  I could go on for ever do a monday night quarter-back analysis of vietnam, therefore I better quit now.  What I do know for sure is that we must never forget VietNam but we must get on with our lifes.  We must get our families back and get off this kick of poor me.<br>
Thank you for allowing me to express my opion.  BYE.
<p><code>-- dmunger@global2000.net  (Dale R. Munger) </code><p>


